        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali120-kilavi">itu piriviṭai yāṟṟāta talaivi mālaippoḻutu kaṇṭu kaḻiya 1āṟṟāḷāyiṉa iṭattut talaivaṉ varavum avaḷatu akamalarcciyuṅ kaṇṭār kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali120">
                <l>aruṭīrnta kāṭciyā ṉaṟaṉōkkā ṉayañceyyāṉ </l>
                <l>veruvuṟa vuyttava ṉeñcampōṟ paipaya </l>
                <l>viruṭūrpu pulampūrak kaṉaicuṭar kalcēra </l>
                <l>vuravuttakai maḻuṅkittaṉ ṉiṭumpaiyā loruvaṉai </l>
                <l>yirappava ṉeñcampōṟ pulleṉṟu puṟamāṟik </l>
                <l>karappava ṉeñcampōṉ maramellā milaikūmpat </l>
                <l>tōṟṟañcāl cekkaruṭ piṟainuti yeyiṟāka </l>
                <l>nāṟṟicaiyu naṭukkuṟūu maṭaṅkaṟ kālaik </l>
                <l>kūṟṟunak katupōlu muṭkuvaru kaṭumālai;</l>
                <l rend="space">mālainī, uḷḷaṅkoṇ ṭakaṉṟavar tuṇaittārāp poḻutiṉkaṇ </l>
                <l>veḷḷamā ṉiṟanōkkik kaṇaitoṭukkuṅ koṭiyāṉpō </l>
                <l>lallaṟpaṭ ṭiruntārai yayarppiya vantāyō;</l>
                <l rend="space">mālainī, īramil kātala rikantaruḷā viṭaṉōkkip </l>
                <l>pōrtolain tiruntāraip pāṭeḷḷi nakuvārpō </l>
                <l>lāraña ruṟṟārai yaṇaṅkiya vantāyō;</l>
                <l rend="space">mālainī, kantātal cāṉṟavar kaḷaitārāp poḻutiṉkaṇ </l>
                <l>ventatōr puṇṇiṉkaṇ vēlkoṇṭu nuḻaippāṉpōṟ </l>
                <l>kāyntanō yuḻappāraik kalakkiya vantāyō;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>iṭaṉiṉ ṟalaittaru miṉṉācey mālai </l>
                <l>tuṉiko ṭuyartīrak kātalar tuṉaitara </l>
                <l>melliyāṉ paruvattu mēṉiṉṟa kaṭumpakai </l>
                <l>yolleṉa nīkki yoruvātu kāttōmpu </l>
                <l>nalliṟai tōṉṟak keṭṭāṅ </l>
                <l>killā kiṉṟā liruḷakat toḷittē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>When, like the heart of one whose sight is without mercy, who does not look at duty,</l>
                <l>who does not act with affection, the [sun whose] glow [is] intense joins the rocks </l>
                <l>so that slowly darkness thickens [and] loneliness creeps up,</l>
                <l>when, like the heart of one who begs from another, because of his misery,</l>
                <l>[his] fitness for strength become blunt, like the heart of someone who hides,</l>
                <l>vainly retreating to the outside, all the trees close [their] leaves,</l>
                <l>at the time of decline when all the four direction experience shivering,</l>
                <l>with as teeth the tips of the crescent moon in the red evening sky worthy of [its] appearance</l>
                <l corresp="1-9">dreadful harsh evening resembles Death who is laughing.</l>
                <l>You, evening, at the time that does not bring [back my] consort, him who departed having taken [my] heart,</l>
                <l>like a cruel man who puts on an arrow aiming at the vital spot of a deer [caught] in the flood,</l>
                <l corresp="10-12">have to come to wear down those who are [already] suffering mishap?</l>
                <l>You, evening, looking [at me] at the time when [my] affectionless lover goes away [and] is inconsiderate,</l>
                <l>like those who, mocking the event, laugh about those who are lost in war,</l>
                <l corresp="13-15">have you come to torment those who [already] have difficult grief?</l>
                <l>You, evening, at the time the one who ought to be [our] prop does not remove [our misery],</l>
                <l>like one who takes a spear [and] puts it into a wound that is [already] burning,</l>
                <l corresp="16-18">have you come to upset those who bear hot pain?</l>
                <l corresp="19">That is to say,</l>
                <l corresp="20">evening who does unpleasant things, <choice><seg>harassing</seg><seg>harasses</seg></choice> [us] without a place [to take refuge in],</l>
                <l corresp="21"><choice><seg>when</seg><seg>While</seg></choice> the lover makes haste to end the loathsome affliction,</l>
                <l corresp="24"><choice><seg>thus gets lost when a good lord appears</seg><seg>as if a good lord visibly got lost</seg></choice></l>
                <l corresp="23"><choice><seg>who without renouncing guards [and] protects,</seg><seg>who would without renouncing guard [and] protect,</seg></choice> repelling fast</l>
                <l corresp="22">the fierce enmity against someone weak that stood on the season,</l>
                <l corresp="25"><choice><seg>[and] becomes nothing, hidden in darkness.</seg><seg>the house has become one that is hidden in darkness.</seg></choice></l>
            </lg>
        </div>
